# 🔒 Linux & Cloud Hardening

A hands-on security hardening project applying CIS Benchmark controls to Linux systems and AWS EC2 instances — covering firewall configuration, IAM least-privilege enforcement, vulnerability scanning, and documented risk posture improvement.

---

## 📌 Overview

Misconfigured systems are the leading cause of cloud breaches. This project systematically hardens Linux and AWS environments using industry-standard benchmarks, validates the posture with OpenVAS vulnerability scans, and documents risk reduction before and after remediation.

**Real hardening. Real scan results. Documented evidence of risk reduction.**

---

## 🎯 Key Features

- 🛡️ **CIS Benchmark hardening** — Linux OS hardened against CIS Level 1 & 2 controls
- ☁️ **AWS EC2 hardening** — IAM least-privilege, security groups, and CloudTrail logging
- 🔥 **Firewall configuration** — UFW/iptables rules enforcing deny-by-default posture
- 🔍 **Vulnerability scanning** — OpenVAS scans pre- and post-hardening to measure improvement
- 📄 **Risk documentation** — structured reports showing before/after security posture

