## 📋 Hardening Controls Applied

### Linux OS (CIS Benchmark)

| Control Area         | Controls Applied |
|---------------------|-----------------|
| SSH Configuration   | PermitRootLogin no, MaxAuthTries 3, key-only auth |
| Password Policy     | Min length 14, complexity requirements, expiry 90 days |
| Filesystem         | noexec on /tmp, /var/tmp, /dev/shm |
| Kernel Parameters  | ASLR enabled, IP forwarding disabled, SYN cookies |
| Logging            | auditd enabled, auth logs retained 90 days |
| Services           | Disabled: telnet, rsh, ftp, cups, avahi |
| Firewall           | UFW default deny inbound/outbound, allow only SSH (22) |

### AWS EC2 / Cloud

| Control Area    | Controls Applied |
|----------------|-----------------|
| IAM            | Least-privilege roles, no wildcard permissions, MFA enforced |
| Security Groups | Deny-by-default, SSH restricted to known IPs only |
| CloudTrail     | Enabled in all regions, S3 log archiving |
| S3             | Block public access, bucket policies, versioning enabled |
| EC2            | No public IPs unless required, IMDSv2 enforced |

